19
00:00:18,439 --> 00:00:20,900
<i>Death and destruction!</i>

20
00:00:20,942 --> 00:00:23,569
<i>Darth Maul and Savage Opress
spread chaos</i>

21
00:00:23,611 --> 00:00:25,780
<i>as they descend on the Outer Rim.</i>

22
00:00:26,113 --> 00:00:28,574
<i>After rescuing his brother from despair,</i>

23
00:00:28,616 --> 00:00:32,119
<i>Savage and Maul murder and pillage
at every turn.</i>

24
00:00:32,537 --> 00:00:34,705
<i>Fueled by rage and vengeance,</i>

25
00:00:34,789 --> 00:00:37,208
<i>they search for meaning
in their new alliance</i>

26
00:00:37,291 --> 00:00:41,963
<i>as reports of their brutal attacks
spread across the galaxy.</i>

27
00:01:07,822 --> 00:01:11,242
Fan out. I want a scan
of the entire perimeter.

28
00:01:12,076 --> 00:01:16,163
SD-357, have you found
anyone in the south passage?

29
00:01:18,916 --> 00:01:21,335
357, where are you?

30
00:01:25,756 --> 00:01:26,966
Intruders!

31
00:01:29,677 --> 00:01:31,929
You are trespassing on Intergalactic...

32
00:02:03,669 --> 00:02:06,714
Look, brother, a fortune.

33
00:02:06,839 --> 00:02:10,343
True fortune will be the demise of Kenobi.

34
00:02:10,384 --> 00:02:14,347
Credit chips are meaningless
without a plan to survive.

35
00:02:14,388 --> 00:02:17,224
The Jedi are hunting us.

36
00:02:17,308 --> 00:02:19,560
We will be forced to make a stand.

37
00:02:19,644 --> 00:02:22,480
And we will deal with them.

38
00:02:22,563 --> 00:02:24,857
They are too many.

39
00:02:24,899 --> 00:02:27,318
To continue, we need one singular vision.

40
00:02:28,569 --> 00:02:30,321
My vision.

41
00:02:30,404 --> 00:02:33,407
Brother, let us share our strength.

42
00:02:34,659 --> 00:02:37,745
There is no need for dominance
between us.

43
00:02:37,828 --> 00:02:44,001
Always two there are, my brother,
a master and an apprentice.

44
00:02:44,085 --> 00:02:47,254
And you are the apprentice.

45
00:02:52,259 --> 00:02:55,930
So it is time for a lesson.

46
00:03:07,441 --> 00:03:09,902
You have grown so powerful.

47
00:03:12,446 --> 00:03:16,117
And I shall complete your training.

48
00:03:16,242 --> 00:03:20,287
Not as your brother, but as your master.

49
00:03:30,131 --> 00:03:34,927
The distress signal is coming from here,
the Meridian sector, Cybloc system.

50
00:03:34,969 --> 00:03:38,472
It is close enough to the earlier attack.

51
00:03:38,597 --> 00:03:40,015
I have a feeling it's them.

52
00:03:49,108 --> 00:03:50,985
They ought to be flush.

53
00:03:51,110 --> 00:03:54,321
Chips were all unlocked.
No way to trace 'em.

54
00:03:54,447 --> 00:03:58,784
All done by the two crabbiest Zabraks
this side of the Hydian.

55
00:03:59,618 --> 00:04:01,829
-They were alone?
-Yep. Yep.

56
00:04:01,871 --> 00:04:05,499
What were they?
A couple of Jedi gone rogue or something?

57
00:04:07,668 --> 00:04:10,296
They're not Jedi.

58
00:04:10,337 --> 00:04:13,507
Do me a favor.
Spark up that lightsaber, would ya?

59
00:04:15,551 --> 00:04:19,346
Mmm-hmm. Well, the droids that
got attacked said that theirs were red.

60
00:04:20,681 --> 00:04:24,226
They are Sith, and we need to find them
before they strike again.

61
00:04:24,351 --> 00:04:26,520
Well, they took my cargo ship.

62
00:04:27,980 --> 00:04:32,193
The droid survivors said they heard
something about the Sertar sector.

63
00:04:38,032 --> 00:04:40,409
What is in the Sertar sector?

64
00:04:40,534 --> 00:04:42,203
That's where Florrum is.

65
00:04:42,328 --> 00:04:44,497
You've been there?

66
00:04:44,538 --> 00:04:47,374
-What can we expect?
-Pirates.

67
00:05:01,889 --> 00:05:04,391
Get me a read out on that ship.

68
00:05:04,433 --> 00:05:07,520
There are life forms aboard.

69
00:05:07,561 --> 00:05:11,190
The main reactor
and hyperdrive generator are down.

70
00:05:11,232 --> 00:05:12,900
I think they're stranded.

71
00:05:13,067 --> 00:05:15,861
And their communications?

72
00:05:15,903 --> 00:05:19,406
Operational but silenced.

73
00:05:20,282 --> 00:05:26,330
We'll kill anyone on board and take the ship.
Let's hope they have a wealth of cargo.

74
00:05:47,476 --> 00:05:50,354
Pure Sansanna spices.

75
00:05:50,437 --> 00:05:53,941
Hondo will be pleased. We drink tonight.

76
00:05:54,275 --> 00:05:56,986
Now find me those life forms.

77
00:05:59,280 --> 00:06:00,364
Jedi!

78
00:06:07,288 --> 00:06:09,373
Do you want to live?

79
00:06:09,790 --> 00:06:12,209
Yes, very badly.

80
00:06:18,674 --> 00:06:21,135
We will make you rich.

81
00:06:21,218 --> 00:06:24,555
Your skills and talents could serve us well.

82
00:06:25,139 --> 00:06:27,141
The choice is yours.

83
00:06:28,142 --> 00:06:30,519
Are you hiring us?

84
00:06:30,644 --> 00:06:32,813
What kind of Jedi are you?

85
00:06:32,855 --> 00:06:35,482
We are not Jedi.

86
00:06:35,524 --> 00:06:40,321
We are lords, crime lords.

87
00:06:40,362 --> 00:06:42,489
We work for Hondo.

88
00:06:42,573 --> 00:06:46,243
You'll have to pay us really well
to get us to betray him.

89
00:06:46,660 --> 00:06:49,997
Money is of no object for men like us.

90
00:06:50,039 --> 00:06:53,667
You will have all that you desire and more

91
00:06:53,709 --> 00:06:56,712
if you pledge yourselves to me.

92
00:06:58,339 --> 00:07:03,052
All right. I'm tired of working
for Hondo anyway.

93
00:07:04,011 --> 00:07:08,515
I'll call up a couple of the boys
and see if they'll join us.

94
00:07:16,607 --> 00:07:21,195
I am certain Captain Hondo
will never throw in with you.

95
00:07:21,612 --> 00:07:26,575
Hondo's base will soon be ours,
and he will not survive this

96
00:07:27,493 --> 00:07:31,372
unless he embraces
the same choice I give you now.

97
00:07:35,626 --> 00:07:37,795
-Ha! I'm in.
-So am I.

98
00:07:37,878 --> 00:07:41,799
I am not sure.
Let's see what Hondo says about that.

99
00:07:46,637 --> 00:07:51,475
<i>Three of your lieutenants
have already sworn allegiance to me.</i>

100
00:07:52,101 --> 00:07:54,311
Traitors! Scum!

101
00:07:56,146 --> 00:07:57,398
I'm so proud,

102
00:07:58,440 --> 00:08:00,484
but so betrayed!

103
00:08:02,486 --> 00:08:05,906
There is a penalty for resistance.

104
00:08:14,623 --> 00:08:16,834
<i>Let me warn you.</i>

105
00:08:16,917 --> 00:08:22,256
<i>You are not the first laser-sword-wielding
maniac I've had to deal with,</i>

106
00:08:23,632 --> 00:08:27,720
<i>and Hondo Ohnaka survives every time!</i>

107
00:08:29,263 --> 00:08:31,181
We shall see.

108
00:08:43,193 --> 00:08:46,113
We have a match on the cargo ship.

109
00:08:46,196 --> 00:08:49,450
It seems Maul and Savage
have picked up a pirate escort.

110
00:08:49,533 --> 00:08:52,453
Maybe to unload the stolen cargo.

111
00:08:52,536 --> 00:08:57,291
I'm not sure the pirate Hondo would have
an alliance with Maul and his brother.

112
00:08:57,374 --> 00:09:00,377
So you know this Hondo personally?

113
00:09:00,919 --> 00:09:03,338
Unfortunately, yes.

114
00:09:05,090 --> 00:09:09,136
Oi, Hondo, there's a Jedi contacting you.

115
00:09:09,219 --> 00:09:11,930
Says his name is Kenobi.

116
00:09:12,014 --> 00:09:13,599
Kenobi? Ha!

117
00:09:14,767 --> 00:09:17,186
My, aren't we popular today?

118
00:09:17,269 --> 00:09:19,897
Put him through. Go, go, go.

119
00:09:20,939 --> 00:09:22,357
<i>Greetings, Hondo.</i>

120
00:09:22,441 --> 00:09:27,446
Greetings? What kind of menace
have you brought to my planet now?

121
00:09:27,529 --> 00:09:29,573
First, you lose this system,

122
00:09:29,656 --> 00:09:33,744
and Grievous comes in
and destroys my entire stronghold,

123
00:09:33,827 --> 00:09:37,539
leaving me here to just rummage
through the leftovers

124
00:09:37,623 --> 00:09:40,209
of my once great empire.

125
00:09:40,292 --> 00:09:44,379
And now, these two horned men show up.

126
00:09:44,463 --> 00:09:47,549
Who are these horny-headed maniacs?

127
00:09:47,633 --> 00:09:49,802
They don't seem like normal Jedi.

128
00:09:49,885 --> 00:09:54,014
<i>Not Jedi, Hondo. Sith.
We tracked them here.</i>

129
00:09:54,098 --> 00:09:59,103
They just threatened to attack
with a group of my men.

130
00:09:59,186 --> 00:10:00,562
My own men!

131
00:10:00,646 --> 00:10:02,731
Yes, we are looking at them right now.

132
00:10:02,815 --> 00:10:06,985
A cargo vessel and three of your star ships.
They are heading toward you, Hondo.

133
00:10:08,445 --> 00:10:11,990
<i>More to the point, are you going
to help me when you get here?</i>

134
00:10:12,074 --> 00:10:13,909
There's nothing we can do about your men,

135
00:10:13,992 --> 00:10:16,829
but we can certainly do something
about the Sith.

136
00:10:16,912 --> 00:10:22,584
<i>Good! I'll deal with my men.
You deal with those tattooed crazies.</i>

137
00:10:22,668 --> 00:10:24,044
Right.

138
00:10:39,893 --> 00:10:45,440
Well, that settles it.
Those traitors are no longer my men.

139
00:10:55,159 --> 00:10:57,786
I want their tongues!

140
00:11:26,148 --> 00:11:28,817
The Jedi, brother, they've found us!

141
00:11:30,694 --> 00:11:34,364
No. It's too soon. My plan isn't finished yet.

142
00:11:35,032 --> 00:11:36,450
Too soon.

143
00:11:46,793 --> 00:11:51,840
Throwing in with pirates now?
Oh, how the mighty Sith have fallen.

144
00:12:35,884 --> 00:12:41,723
No. I have plans, Kenobi,
and you will not stand in my way this time.

145
00:13:05,539 --> 00:13:07,207
No!

146
00:13:24,141 --> 00:13:25,892
Kenobi, this way!

147
00:13:43,201 --> 00:13:47,748
Take this cannon down the hall.
We will ambush those traitors there.

148
00:13:53,837 --> 00:13:57,382
-Where are the rest of your men?
-They are setting up an ambush.

149
00:13:57,466 --> 00:14:00,761
We can use your help.
Where is the other Jedi?

150
00:14:01,136 --> 00:14:03,388
She's dead.

151
00:14:03,472 --> 00:14:06,892
She's...
They are too powerful for even you?

152
00:14:08,393 --> 00:14:10,896
I am semi-speechless!

153
00:14:10,979 --> 00:14:14,024
I think they went this way. Over here.

154
00:14:14,107 --> 00:14:15,650
I shall draw the brothers away.

155
00:14:15,734 --> 00:14:18,570
Once that's done,
blast the passageway closed.

156
00:14:18,653 --> 00:14:21,656
And leave you alone with the two crazies?

157
00:14:22,657 --> 00:14:23,742
Well, okay.

158
00:14:28,413 --> 00:14:29,831
Retreat! Retreat!

159
00:14:31,416 --> 00:14:33,126
Do not let them escape.

160
00:14:46,056 --> 00:14:47,099
Now!

161
00:14:54,898 --> 00:14:55,941
Surrender.

162
00:14:56,650 --> 00:15:00,570
We are two,
and you are no match for us both.

163
00:15:01,696 --> 00:15:03,532
You are mistaken.

164
00:15:08,328 --> 00:15:12,165
Are you still willing to fight me?

165
00:15:12,249 --> 00:15:15,377
The horned men aren't interested
in helping you.

166
00:15:16,294 --> 00:15:19,589
They are only interested in Kenobi.

167
00:15:45,699 --> 00:15:49,494
They promised us wealth and power, boss.
Please forgive us.

168
00:15:49,995 --> 00:15:53,748
Please don't kill us. We beg of you!

169
00:15:53,832 --> 00:15:58,170
Kill you? I would not kill you.

170
00:15:58,253 --> 00:16:03,758
Everyone, the horned men's ship
is filled with valuable goods.

171
00:16:03,842 --> 00:16:09,514
As your restored leader,
I say we celebrate our reunification.

172
00:16:09,598 --> 00:16:12,726
- To the landing pad !
- Right!

173
00:16:30,368 --> 00:16:31,953
Savage!

174
00:16:39,711 --> 00:16:41,505
Come, my apprentice.

175
00:16:41,588 --> 00:16:46,843
This plan has failed,
but we will have another opportunity.

176
00:17:00,148 --> 00:17:02,275
Jiro, ready the men. We're leaving.

177
00:17:02,359 --> 00:17:05,904
My men aren't going anywhere with you.

178
00:17:05,987 --> 00:17:09,282
Look at them. How powerful can they be?

179
00:17:09,366 --> 00:17:12,285
They are running away from Kenobi.

180
00:17:12,369 --> 00:17:16,039
Filth, you will pay for your insolence.

181
00:17:16,414 --> 00:17:18,500
Insolence!

182
00:17:18,583 --> 00:17:22,170
We are pirates!
We don't even know what that means.

183
00:17:22,254 --> 00:17:23,338
Open fire!

184
00:17:24,297 --> 00:17:29,636
If we kill those two,
their riches will be ours.

185
00:18:27,986 --> 00:18:31,615
Our engines have been compromised.
Get to the escape pod.

186
00:18:31,698 --> 00:18:33,491
It's too late.

187
00:18:34,326 --> 00:18:36,119
Trust me, apprentice.

188
00:19:00,143 --> 00:19:03,021
Well, Kenobi, let's get out there

189
00:19:03,063 --> 00:19:07,734
and see what riches have fallen
from the sky for me and you.

190
00:19:10,236 --> 00:19:12,864
-Shall we?
-Very well.

191
00:19:35,970 --> 00:19:38,223
There's no sign of those two, boss.

192
00:19:38,723 --> 00:19:43,269
Well, if the condition
of these goods is any indication,

193
00:19:44,437 --> 00:19:46,231
your friends have been vaporized.

194
00:19:46,606 --> 00:19:48,441
I wouldn't be so sure.

195
00:19:48,566 --> 00:19:51,444
I cut one of them in half once,
and he survived.

196
00:19:51,945 --> 00:19:54,114
Well, isn't that interesting.

197
00:20:01,162 --> 00:20:04,958
I think we have closure
on this matter, Master Kenobi.

198
00:20:05,083 --> 00:20:07,127
I disagree, Chancellor.

199
00:20:07,168 --> 00:20:10,630
Everything we've learned from this
is that the Sith are persistent.

200
00:20:10,672 --> 00:20:12,132
They will not die.

201
00:20:12,632 --> 00:20:15,385
I understand your reservations,
Master Kenobi,

202
00:20:15,468 --> 00:20:19,806
but I am afraid we can no longer allow
this personal matter of yours

203
00:20:19,889 --> 00:20:21,391
to be a Republic concern.

204
00:20:21,474 --> 00:20:26,187
It does not appear this Darth Maul
is a direct threat to the Republic.

205
00:20:26,312 --> 00:20:29,816
We need to redirect your efforts
to the cause at hand,

206
00:20:29,899 --> 00:20:34,320
stopping Count Dooku
and thus ending the Clone Wars.

207
00:20:34,863 --> 00:20:37,741
Maul was trying to build an army of pirates.

208
00:20:37,824 --> 00:20:41,327
So let him. Let him play with the rabble.

209
00:20:41,411 --> 00:20:43,830
They're just petty crooks.

210
00:20:43,913 --> 00:20:47,834
It is of no relevance to the Senate
compared to the Separatist threat.

211
00:20:48,585 --> 00:20:50,336
Good day, gentlemen.

212
00:20:53,423 --> 00:20:55,842
Something is stirring in the underworld.

213
00:20:55,884 --> 00:20:58,344
The crime families have had
too much free rein

214
00:20:58,428 --> 00:21:01,181
since the Jedi have been distracted
by the Clone War.

215
00:21:01,264 --> 00:21:06,102
I fear it is a fertile place for Maul to flourish
if he has indeed survived.

216
00:21:06,561 --> 00:21:07,854
Hmm.

217
00:21:07,937 --> 00:21:10,023
Right you may be, Obi-Wan,

218
00:21:10,106 --> 00:21:13,443
but heed the words
of the Chancellor we must.

219
00:21:13,526 --> 00:21:18,823
A personal matter this is for you.
Clouded your judgment may be.

220
00:21:18,907 --> 00:21:23,828
In time, if he lives,
reveal himself again, Maul will.

221
00:21:24,120 --> 00:21:26,915
And then swiftly we shall act.

222
00:21:26,939 --> 00:21:31,939
http://hiqve.com/

